United Illuminating Co saidthat if the Department of Utility Controls approves an earningsstipulation agreement submitted March 18, it will reducethrough accounting procedures its 1987 noncash earnings by 16mln dlrs or 1.15 dlr per share.    For the two month period ended February 28, 1987, it saidthe amount of the reduction would amount to 19 cts per share.Earlier, it reported net income for the two-month period of23.1 mln dlrs of 1.51 dlr a share.    United said the approval would lead it to an equity returnlevel comparable with the electric utility industry average. Reuter&#3;